                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d488">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Italy/301: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-02T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 2, 1936—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 2—8:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>503. My 397, October 1, noon.<note n="52" xml:id="d488fn52">Not printed.</note>
                    From a variety of well-informed but unofficial sources it is reported that the
                    Italian Government is preparing to inaugurate discussions in Washington looking
                    toward the settlement of its war debts. It is even said that the Minister of
                    Finance has stated that Italy will propose some form of token payment.</p>
                <p>When these reports have been brought to my attention I have refrained from making
                    any comment whatsoever.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
